---
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionDivider from '../components/SectionDivider.astro';
import reviews from '../data/google-reviews.json';
---

<Layout
  title="Voice Coaching in Lacey, WA"
  description="Singing, speaking, and ensemble coaching from a 40-year voice expert in Lacey, WA. Personalized lessons that help you understand and master your unique voice."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <span class="hero-eyebrow">Master Your Voice</span>
          <h1>Your voice already has something to say. I help you say it clearly.</h1>
          <p class="hero-promise">Helping singers and speakers develop a voice that is reliable, expressive, and authentically theirs.</p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
            <a href="/about/" class="btn-link">Learn more about my approach →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image">
          <img src="/images/hero-ted.webp" alt="Ted Chamberlain, voice coach" class="hero-photo" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credentials Bar -->
  <section class="credentials-bar">
    <div class="container">
      <p>Four decades of teaching • Award-winning performer • Recognized among Washington's top vocal instructors</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider variant="wave" topColor="var(--color-navy-deep)" bottomColor="var(--color-off-white)" />

  <!-- Value Proposition Section -->
  <section class="value-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow reveal">
      <h2 class="decorated-heading">Voice coaching that starts with you</h2>
      <p class="drop-cap">Voice coaching is personal. I take time to understand where you are, where you want to go, and what's getting in the way. When you understand how your voice works, everything else falls into place. That's what I help you build—skills that last.</p>
      <blockquote class="pull-quote">When you understand how your voice works, everything else falls into place.</blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three Paths Section -->
  <section class="paths-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="decorated-heading reveal">How can I help?</h2>
      <p class="section-intro reveal">I work with individuals and groups at every level. Choose the path that fits your goals.</p>

      <div class="paths-grid reveal-stagger">
        <div class="path-card reveal">
          <h3>Singing</h3>
          <p class="path-subtitle">Vocal and performance coaching for singers, typically ages 14 and up.</p>
          <p>Every singer arrives with different goals. Some want to build technique from the ground up. Others are working through a specific challenge or preparing for something important. I meet you where you are and design lessons around what matters most to you—your style, your experience, your voice.</p>
          <a href="/singing/" class="path-link">Explore Singing Lessons →</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="path-card reveal">
          <h3>Speaking</h3>
          <p class="path-subtitle">Voice and performance coaching for clear, confident, authentic communication.</p>
          <p>The way you speak shapes how your ideas land. I work with professionals, educators, and leaders who want to communicate with greater clarity and presence. Together, we address the physical foundations of voice—breath support, resonance, pacing, and projection—so your message comes through with the impact it deserves.</p>
          <a href="/speaking/" class="path-link">Explore Speaking Coaching →</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="path-card reveal">
          <h3>Ensembles</h3>
          <p class="path-subtitle">Vocal and performance coaching for groups seeking unity, efficiency, and expressive sound.</p>
          <p>Strong ensemble singing starts with strong individual skills. I work with choirs, quartets, and vocal groups to develop tuning, unity, and authentic performance presence. Whether you're preparing for competition or simply want to connect more deeply as an ensemble, I can help your group find its voice.</p>
          <a href="/ensembles/" class="path-link">Explore Ensemble Coaching →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider variant="curve" topColor="var(--color-white)" bottomColor="var(--color-navy-deep)" />

  <!-- Ecosystem Showcase Section -->
  <section class="ecosystem-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="decorated-heading decorated-heading--light reveal">Voice mastery, many paths</h2>
      <p class="section-intro reveal">Personal coaching is the heart of what I do. It's also part of a larger picture — a complete approach to voice mastery that includes frameworks, tools, education, and community.</p>

      <div class="ecosystem-grid reveal-stagger">
        <div class="eco-card eco-avf reveal">
          <h3>The Adaptive Voice Framework™</h3>
          <p>The teaching framework behind everything I do — now available as a nearly 700-page book. AVF™ organizes how voices work into a clear, practical system any singer or speaker can use.</p>
          <a href="/avf/" class="eco-link avf-link">Learn about AVF →</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="eco-card eco-pass reveal">
          <h3>PASS Profile™</h3>
          <p>A professional communication assessment I created to help people understand how they naturally communicate. Discover your unique patterns, strengths, and style — then use that knowledge with purpose.</p>
          <a href="/pass-profile/" class="eco-link pass-link">Take the PASS Profile →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="eco-card eco-intlab reveal">
          <h3>Intonation Lab</h3>
          <p>A browser-based ear training tool that uses real-time pitch detection and just intonation targets to help singers develop precise intonation. Visual feedback, 52 exercises, and group licenses for ensembles.</p>
          <a href="/intonation-lab/" class="eco-link">Explore Intonation Lab →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="eco-card eco-riser reveal">
          <h3>Riser Chart</h3>
          <p>A drag-and-drop riser placement tool built for chorus directors. Up to 24 voice parts, singer photos, timbre rings, batch editing, groups, events, unlimited formations, and branded exports — all from your browser.</p>
          <a href="/riser-chart/" class="eco-link">Explore Riser Chart →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="eco-card eco-health reveal">
          <h3>Vocal Health</h3>
          <p>Your voice is an instrument that deserves good care. I share what I've learned about keeping voices healthy — from daily habits and home remedies to conditioning exercises and knowing when to seek help.</p>
          <a href="/vocal-health/" class="eco-link">Explore Vocal Health →</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="eco-card eco-workshops reveal">
          <h3>Workshops & Presentations</h3>
          <p>Group learning experiences for singers, speakers, and organizations. From my signature AVF Workshop Series to conference sessions and custom events — I bring voice education to groups of all sizes.</p>
          <a href="/workshops/" class="eco-link">View Workshop Options →</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="eco-card eco-blog reveal">
          <h3>Blog</h3>
          <p>Ideas, insights, and practical guidance on vocal technique, performance, health, and the mindset behind lasting growth. New posts regularly.</p>
          <a href="/blog/" class="eco-link">Read the Blog →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider variant="wave" topColor="var(--color-navy-deep)" bottomColor="var(--color-off-white)" />

  <!-- About Preview Section -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="about-image reveal-left">
          <img src="/images/ted-headshot.webp" alt="Ted Chamberlain" class="about-photo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>
        <div class="about-content reveal-right">
          <h2>A bit about me</h2>
          <p>I'm Ted Chamberlain. I've spent my career studying voices—how they work, why they struggle, and what helps them grow. I've taught in classrooms, rehearsal halls, and private studios. I've coached beginners and professionals, soloists and ensembles.</p>
          <p>What I've learned is this: every voice is different, and every voice can improve. The path forward depends on understanding what's actually happening when you sing or speak—and then making small, specific changes that add up over time.</p>
          <p>That's the kind of work I love. If you're ready to understand your voice better, I'd be glad to help.</p>
          <a href="/about/" class="about-link">Read my full story →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reviews Section (Google Reviews Carousel) -->
  <section class="reviews-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="reveal">What people are saying</h2>
      <div class="google-rating-bar reveal">
        <svg class="google-g-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M22.56 12.25c0-.78-.07-1.53-.2-2.25H12v4.26h5.92a5.06 5.06 0 01-2.2 3.32v2.77h3.57c2.08-1.92 3.28-4.74 3.28-8.1z" fill="#4285F4"/>
          <path d="M12 23c2.97 0 5.46-.98 7.28-2.66l-3.57-2.77c-.98.66-2.23 1.06-3.71 1.06-2.86 0-5.29-1.93-6.16-4.53H2.18v2.84C3.99 20.53 7.7 23 12 23z" fill="#34A853"/>
          <path d="M5.84 14.09c-.22-.66-.35-1.36-.35-2.09s.13-1.43.35-2.09V7.07H2.18C1.43 8.55 1 10.22 1 12s.43 3.45 1.18 4.93l2.85-2.22.81-.62z" fill="#FBBC05"/>
          <path d="M12 5.38c1.62 0 3.06.56 4.21 1.64l3.15-3.15C17.45 2.09 14.97 1 12 1 7.7 1 3.99 3.47 2.18 7.07l3.66 2.84c.87-2.6 3.3-4.53 6.16-4.53z" fill="#EA4335"/>
        </svg>
        <span class="rating-number">5.0</span>
        <span class="rating-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span>
        <span class="rating-count">31 Google reviews</span>
      </div>
      <div class="carousel-wrapper reveal" aria-roledescription="carousel" aria-label="Customer reviews">
        <button class="carousel-btn carousel-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="carousel-track">
          {reviews.map((review) => (
            <div class="review-card" role="group" aria-label={`Review by ${review.name}`}>
              <div class="review-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div>
              <p class="review-text">{review.text}</p>
              <div class="review-footer">
                <div class="review-author">
                  <span class="author-name">{review.name}</span>
                  <span class="author-date">{review.date}</span>
                </div>
                <svg class="google-g-small" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" aria-label="Google Review">
                  <path d="M22.56 12.25c0-.78-.07-1.53-.2-2.25H12v4.26h5.92a5.06 5.06 0 01-2.2 3.32v2.77h3.57c2.08-1.92 3.28-4.74 3.28-8.1z" fill="#4285F4"/>
                  <path d="M12 23c2.97 0 5.46-.98 7.28-2.66l-3.57-2.77c-.98.66-2.23 1.06-3.71 1.06-2.86 0-5.29-1.93-6.16-4.53H2.18v2.84C3.99 20.53 7.7 23 12 23z" fill="#34A853"/>
                  <path d="M5.84 14.09c-.22-.66-.35-1.36-.35-2.09s.13-1.43.35-2.09V7.07H2.18C1.43 8.55 1 10.22 1 12s.43 3.45 1.18 4.93l2.85-2.22.81-.62z" fill="#FBBC05"/>
                  <path d="M12 5.38c1.62 0 3.06.56 4.21 1.64l3.15-3.15C17.45 2.09 14.97 1 12 1 7.7 1 3.99 3.47 2.18 7.07l3.66 2.84c.87-2.6 3.3-4.53 6.16-4.53z" fill="#EA4335"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <button class="carousel-btn carousel-next" aria-label="Next reviews">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline></svg>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews-cta reveal">
        <a href="https://go.r-rev.com/tedsvoiceacademy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-review">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon-inline"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"></polygon></svg>
          Share Your Experience
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Ted's Voice Academy",
      "aggregateRating": {
        "@type": "AggregateRating",
        "ratingValue": "5.0",
        "bestRating": "5",
        "worstRating": "1",
        "ratingCount": "31",
        "reviewCount": "31"
      }
    })} />
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline>
      (function() {
        var track = document.querySelector('.carousel-track');
        if (!track) return;
        var prevBtn = document.querySelector('.carousel-prev');
        var nextBtn = document.querySelector('.carousel-next');
        var cards = track.querySelectorAll('.review-card');
        if (!cards.length) return;

        var autoInterval;
        var isPaused = false;
        var pauseTimer;

        function getScrollAmount() {
          var card = cards[0];
          var gap = parseFloat(getComputedStyle(track).gap) || 24;
          return card.offsetWidth + gap;
        }

        function scrollNext() {
          var amount = getScrollAmount();
          var maxScroll = track.scrollWidth - track.clientWidth;
          if (track.scrollLeft >= maxScroll - 5) {
            track.scrollTo({ left: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
          } else {
            track.scrollBy({ left: amount, behavior: 'smooth' });
          }
        }

        function scrollPrev() {
          var amount = getScrollAmount();
          if (track.scrollLeft <= 5) {
            track.scrollTo({ left: track.scrollWidth - track.clientWidth, behavior: 'smooth' });
          } else {
            track.scrollBy({ left: -amount, behavior: 'smooth' });
          }
        }

        function startAuto() {
          if (autoInterval) clearInterval(autoInterval);
          autoInterval = setInterval(function() {
            if (!isPaused) scrollNext();
          }, 5000);
        }

        function pauseFor(ms) {
          isPaused = true;
          if (pauseTimer) clearTimeout(pauseTimer);
          pauseTimer = setTimeout(function() { isPaused = false; }, ms);
        }

        track.addEventListener('mouseenter', function() { isPaused = true; });
        track.addEventListener('mouseleave', function() { isPaused = false; });
        track.addEventListener('touchstart', function() { isPaused = true; }, { passive: true });
        track.addEventListener('touchend', function() { pauseFor(5000); }, { passive: true });

        if (prevBtn) {
          prevBtn.addEventListener('click', function() { scrollPrev(); pauseFor(8000); });
        }
        if (nextBtn) {
          nextBtn.addEventListener('click', function() { scrollNext(); pauseFor(8000); });
        }

        document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() {
          isPaused = document.hidden;
        });

        startAuto();
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <SectionDivider variant="angle" topColor="var(--color-white)" bottomColor="var(--color-navy-deep)" />

  <!-- Final CTA Section -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <h2>Ready to get started?</h2>
      <p>The first step is telling me a bit about yourself. Fill out the form below and I'll be in touch to schedule a conversation.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section */
  .hero {
    background:
      url('/images/noise-texture.png') repeat,
      linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy-deep) 0%, var(--color-navy-medium) 100%);
    background-size: 200px 200px, 100% 100%;
    background-blend-mode: soft-light, normal;
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .hero-promise {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hero-image {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* Hero entrance animations */
  @keyframes heroTextIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(-30px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); }
  }

  @keyframes heroPhotoIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(1.06); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
  }

  .hero-content {
    animation: heroTextIn 1s ease-out 0.2s both;
  }

  .hero-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 500px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    animation: heroPhotoIn 1.2s ease-out 0.5s both;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .hero-content,
    .hero-photo {
      animation: none;
    }
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    border: none;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--color-gold-bright);
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--color-gold-hover);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(212, 168, 75, 0.3);
  }

  .btn-link {
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .btn-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Container Narrow */
  .container-narrow {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Credentials Bar */
  .credentials-bar {
    background:
      url('/images/noise-texture.png') repeat,
      linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy-medium) 0%, var(--color-navy-deep) 100%);
    background-size: 200px 200px, 100% 100%;
    background-blend-mode: soft-light, normal;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(212, 168, 75, 0.15);
  }

